config CRABULIK_ADC_DPAD
    bool "Resistor-ladder 5-way d-pad read on one ADC channel"
    default n
    select ADC
    help
      Reads a passive resistor-ladder 5-way control (e.g. a CaddxFPV OSD menu
      board) on a single ADC channel and sends a keycode per direction. Each
      direction pulls the analog line to a distinct voltage band; the driver
      thresholds the reading and emits the mapped key.

      Requires an ADC channel node labelled `dpad_chan` in the shield overlay and
      an external pull-up resistor from the signal wire to 3.3V. See
      modules/zmk-adc-dpad/README.md for wiring, the overlay snippet, and the
      calibration procedure.

config CRABULIK_ADC_DPAD_LOG_MV
    bool "Log measured d-pad millivolts (calibration aid)"
    depends on CRABULIK_ADC_DPAD
    default n
    help
      Logs the measured voltage and selected band on every poll. Build a logging
      firmware, press each direction, and read the values to set the thresholds.
